    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "WHY HARVEY\n\nAt Harvey, we’re transforming how legal and professional services operate — not incrementally, but end-to-end. By combining frontier agentic AI, an enterprise-grade platform, and deep domain expertise, we’re reshaping how critical knowledge work gets done for decades to come.\n\nThis is a rare chance to help build a generational company at a true inflection point. With 1000+ customers in 60+ countries, strong product-market fit, and world-class investor support, we’re scaling fast and defining a new category in real time. The work is ambitious, the bar is high, and the opportunity for growth — personal, professional, and financial — is unmatched.\n\nOur team is sharp, motivated, and deeply committed to the mission. We move fast, operate with intensity, and take real ownership of the problems we tackle — from early thinking to long-term outcomes. We stay close to our customers — from leadership to engineers — and work together to solve real problems with urgency and care. If you thrive in ambiguity, push for excellence, and want to help shape the future of work alongside others who raise the bar, we invite you to build with us.\n\nAt Harvey, the future of professional services is being written today — and we’re just getting started.\n\n\nROLE OVERVIEW\n\nHarvey is redefining what’s possible in legal work by combining cutting-edge AI with intuitive product experiences. As we scale rapidly and take on increasingly complex use cases, we’re expanding our product engineering team to accelerate our ability to ship fast, delight users, and build infrastructure that scales with us.\n\nAs an Engineering Manager for Product Engineering, you’ll lead teams of fullstack engineers building the core product surfaces that lawyers and legal professionals use every day—from complex workflows and collaboration tools to elegant user interfaces powered by sophisticated backend systems. This role is equal parts product intuition and technical execution. You’ll be trusted to make fast, high-quality decisions, ship impactful features, and grow a team that embodies engineering excellence.\n\nWe move with urgency, bias toward simplicity, and expect our leaders to be hands-on when needed. If you’re energized by ownership, decisive execution, and solving real user problems, we'd love to hear from you.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Lead fullstack engineering team(s) building user-facing features across our web product.\n\n - Collaborate closely with Design, Product, and AI teams to identify and execute on high-impact initiatives.\n\n - Help define and evolve the architecture for a fast-moving, AI-powered application.\n\n - Hire, grow, and retain exceptional engineers who thrive in a high-trust, high-impact environment.\n\n - Foster a culture of simplicity, quality, and continuous improvement.\n\n - Contribute to code and architecture reviews, unblock teams, and lead by example when needed.\n\n - Work closely with cross-functional partners to align product initiatives with company goals.\n\n\nWHAT YOU HAVE\n\n - 2+ years of experience in a software engineering management role leading fullstack product engineering teams, preferably in high-growth environments.\n\n - 5+ years of experience as a fullstack or backend product engineer.\n\n - A track record of leading high-performing, engaged engineering teams.\n\n - Strong product sense and an instinct for balancing speed, quality, and user impact.\n\n - Experience with modern frontend frameworks (e.g. React) and backend systems (e.g. Python, Node, Go).\n\n - A plus: Exposure to AI-powered applications or complex internal tools.\n\n\nCOMPENSATION RANGE\n\n$260,000 - $330,000 USD\n\n\nDEPENDING ON YOUR LOCATION, AN APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICE MAY APPLY TO YOU. YOU CAN FIND ALL OF OUR APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICES [HERE https://www.notion.so/harveyai/Harvey-Candidate-Privacy-Policies-319ac3fcdd7a803bb807d5094f249922].\n\n#LI-ML1\n\nHarvey is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity/expression, national origin, disability, age, genetic information, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy or related condition, or any other basis protected by law.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made by emailing accommodations@harvey.ai",
